<showme.pack xmlns="Compositor"
             xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
             id="Exa_LinearEqsSolveFromRREF"
             xsi:schemaLocation="Compositor file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Compositor.xsd">
	  <texsupport href="../LinearAlgebraTeXSupport.xml"/>
	  <title>Solving from Row Reduced Echelon Form - Example</title>
	  <caption>Solving from RREF - Example</caption>
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Find all solutions of the system of 3 linear equations in 7 variables below.</para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>
					
					\begin{array}{rcr}
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}x_1}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_2}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_3}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}x_4}\ -\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x_5}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_6}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_7} &amp; = &amp; 4 \\
%
\colorbox{lightgreen}{0}{\color{red}x_1}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{0}{\color{red}x_2}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{1}{\color{red}x_3}\ -\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_4}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$4$}{\color{red}x_5} \ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_6}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x_7} &amp; = &amp; -2 \\
%
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_1}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_2}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_3}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_4}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_5}\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}x_6}\ -\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_7} &amp; = &amp; 3 \\
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			      </math.display>
		    </statement.showme>
		    <answer.showme type="Solution">
         <answer.showme.block>
            <answer.showme.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>The <strong>solutions of the first equation</strong> can be found by choosing freely number values for all variables, except for <math>
                        <latex>x_1</latex>
                     </math>, and then defining</para.body>
               </para>
			
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
					{\color{red}x_1}\ :=\ 4\ -\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{2}{\color{red}x_2} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{1}{\color{red}x_4} + \colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x_5} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_7}
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			
			            <para>
                  <para.body>The <strong>solutions of the second equation</strong> can be found by choosing freely number values for all variables, except for <math>
                        <latex>x_3</latex>
                     </math>, and then defining</para.body>
               </para>
			
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
					{\color{red}x_3}\ :=\ -2\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_4} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$4$}{\color{red}x_5} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x_7}
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			
			            <para>
                  <para.body>The <strong>solutions of the third equation</strong> can be found by choosing freely number values for all variables, except for <math>
                        <latex>x_6</latex>
                     </math>, and then defining</para.body>
               </para>
			
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
					{\color{red}x_6}\ :=\ 3\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_7}
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Accordingly, we find the <strong>simultaneous solutions of the system of equations</strong> by choosing freely number values for all variables, except for <math>
                        <latex>x_1,x_3,x_6</latex>
                     </math>, and then defining</para.body>
               </para>
			
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
					\aligned
{\color{red}x_1}\ &amp;:=\phantom{\ -} 4\ -\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{2}{\color{red}x_2} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}x_4} + \colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x_5} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_7} \\
%
{\color{red}x_3}\ &amp;:=\ -2\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_4} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$4$}{\color{red}x_5} - \colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x_7} \\
%
{\color{red}x_6}\ &amp;:=\phantom{\ -} 3\ +\ \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}x_7}
\endaligned
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			
			            <para>
                  <para.body>For example, choosing</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>{\color{red}x_2}:=3,\quad {\color{red}x_4}:=-2,\quad {\color{red}x_5}:=-1,\quad {\color{red}x_7}:=5</latex>
			            </math.display>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>we obtain the specific solution  <math>
                        <latex>(-13,3,-17,-2,-1,13,5)</latex>
                     </math>.</para.body>
               </para>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>In general, arbitrarily chosen number values for each of <math>
                        <latex>r,s,t,u</latex>
                     </math> yields a solution of the given system of linear equations of the form</para.body>
               </para>
			            <ol>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_1 := 4 - 2r - s + 3t - 2u</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_2 := r</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_3 := -2 + 2s-4t-3u</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_4 := s</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_5 := t</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_6 := 3 + 2u</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>x_7 := u</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
			            </ol>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Thus each solution of the given system determine a vector in <math>
                        <latex>\RNr[7]</latex>
                     </math> of the form</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
\begin{array}{l}
(4-2r-s+3t-2u,r,-2+2s-4t-2u,s,t,3+2u,u)\ = \\
(4,0,-2,0,0,3,0) + r\cdot (-2,1,0,0,0,0,0) + s\cdot (-1,0,2,1,0,0,0)\ + \\
\ + t\cdot (3,0,-4,0,1,0,0) + u\cdot (-2,0,-2,0,0,2,1)
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			
			
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Once again, here <math>
                        <latex>r,s,t,u</latex>
                     </math> are arbitrary numbers in <math>
                        <latex>\RNr</latex>
                     </math>. These four numbers are completely independent of one another. We say that the solution space of the given system is the space spanned the vectors</para.body>
               </para>
			            <ul>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>(-2,1,0,0,0,0,0)</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>(-1,0,2,1,0,0,0)</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>(3,0,-4,0,1,0,0)</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>
                           <math>
                              <latex>(-2,0,-2,0,0,2,1)</latex>
                           </math>
                        </para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
			            </ul>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>shifted by the vector <math>
                        <latex>(4,0,-2,0,0,3,0)</latex>
                     </math>.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.showme.block.body>
         </answer.showme.block>
      </answer.showme>
	  </showme>
	
</showme.pack>
